Oct 20 2009 	Great place to stay but the Loop is dead in the evenings	The location is great for sightseeing in the downtown area of Chicago. 2 blocks from the Sears Tower, an easy walk to the Art Institute. We hardly even used the subway. BUT the Loop, with the exception of the Theatre District, is dead for the most part in the evenings. Since it's not a very residential area, most of the stores and restaurants shut down. We were there Friday to Sunday, not sure if this holds true all week, though.The hotel itself was very comfortable, the room was spacious. In fact, it was a little empty; they could have easily added a nice couch to ours. A long desk under the window was great for setting up my laptop (the free wifi was effortlessly easy to use). The staff was very nice and helpful (even if they didn't have any stamps for my postcards). The free breakfast spread was outstanding (though I wish they had skim milk and other fat-free stuff). Business and fitness centers were easily accessible in the basement.My one big complaint about the room was that it had a shower stall but no tub. I prefer a tub for a nice bath. I can live without it, but the shower in this case leaked all over the bathroom floor. Bad design. Quit trying to be so &quot;modern&quot;.	
